  Bugs (Real, Silent Failures)

  1. Import doesn't persist the Playbook

  File: app.js:849–856

  importVault() sets state.playbook in memory but never writes to db.playbook. saveState() only touches db.ideas and db.settings — playbook has its own table. On next page load, loadState() reads db.playbook and restores the
  pre-import entries, silently discarding the import.

  ▎ Fix: After import, do await db.playbook.clear(); await db.playbook.bulkAdd(state.playbook.map(({id:_, ...e}) => e)) and re-assign the returned IDs.

  ---
  2. Karma farming — Morning Boot has no same-day guard

  File: app.js:479–505

  closeDay() is protected by if (state.dayLocked) return. startDay() is not. You can go to Morning Boot and press "Start the day" multiple times on the same day, earning +5 karma each time. The dayLocked flag only gates the
  evening.

  ▎ Fix: In startDay(), add if (state.lastBootDate === todayISO()) { showToast('Day already started', 'info'); return; } before committing.

  ---
  3. Potential field casing is inconsistent

  File: app.js:522–531 vs app.js:32–37

  New ideas captured via the form use btn.dataset.value → 'low', 'medium', 'high' (lowercase). Seed data, edit modal selects, and Dexie-restored data use 'High', 'Medium', 'Low' (title case). The badge CSS class uses
  .toLowerCase() so rendering works, but filtering/sorting on potential would produce two buckets for the same value.

  ▎ Fix: Normalize on capture: capitalize first letter in saveIdea(). Or change all option values in the edit modal to lowercase — pick one casing and enforce it.

