  Structural Observations

  7. saveState() rewrites the entire vault on every karma change

  File: app.js:70–88

  updateKarma() calls saveState() which does db.ideas.clear() + db.ideas.bulkPut(state.vault) — a full table wipe and rewrite — even though karma is just one scalar in the settings table. For <100 ideas this is fine, but it's
  architecturally wasteful.

  ▎ Consider: Split into saveSettings() (fast, settings-only) and saveVault() (vault-only). Call saveSettings() from updateKarma(), closeDay(). Call saveVault() from logProgress(), saveIdea(), saveEdit(), deleteIdea().

  ---
  8. Category is multi-select but treated as single-value everywhere

  File: app.js:519, app.js:290–310, app.js:393

  The chip UI allows selecting multiple categories, and they're joined with ', ' into a string. But badge rendering does idea.category.toLowerCase() as a CSS class — "App, System" becomes class badge app, system which is
  invalid. Vault table shows it as one cell, not multiple badges. The data model says category: string, not category: string[].

  ▎ Fix (simple): Make category single-select (chips behave like radio buttons — clicking one deselects others). One line change in toggleChip().

